VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'GitHub is coming soon. So, it looks like they are planning to open source this, which is fantastic. For now, if you\'re interested in reading further, I\'ll link to this main page in the description below. All right, next up, this AI is'

[29:45] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'pretty cool. It\'s called DocToLora and TextToLora from Sakana AI. And this is a way to compress a document or some text instructions that you want the model to'

[29:57] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'use again and again more efficiently without you having to, you know, copy and paste the entire document or text instructions into your prompt. So, first, let me give you some background on the problem. You see, for most large language models today, they often forget'

[30:10] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'documents or instructions or things that you give it if you chat with it for a long time. So, in order to solve this, you need to like copy and paste the original document or instructions into the prompt again. It doesn\'t really have'

[30:23] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'a long-term memory. So, what they\'ve done here is they\'ve introduced two new methods on how you can actually compress information that you want it to remember into some fine-tuned smaller models called LoRAs. In particular, they'

[30:36] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'propose two methods. One is to convert a doc into a LoRA, and another one is to convert text instructions into Laura\'s. So, here\'s how it works. Let\'s say you want to upload a document for it to analyze. Well, instead of just copying'

[30:49] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'and pasting the entire document into the prompt, this doc to Laura method basically trains a hyper network or basically a small helper neural network to generate a Laura that houses this document. So, next when you\'re chatting'

[31:02] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'with AI and you want to reference the document, instead of pasting the entire document, you can just reference this Laura, which is a lot more compressed and efficient and it\'s able to answer questions about the document without'

[31:14] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'seeing the entire document. So, by capturing the document into this Laura adapter, it feels like it has a persistent memory of this. And the advantage of this method is it can answer you faster, the model doesn\'t'

[31:26] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'have to reread the whole document every time, and this also works with really long documents, much longer than the model\'s usual context window limit. And here\'s an extra cool thing. They also demonstrated that this doc to Laura'

[31:39] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'method can also encode information from images in a document into the Laura, so that even a pure text model with no vision capabilities is able to answer questions about the image without having'

[31:51] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'ever seen the image. Pretty cool. So, that\'s just doc to Laura, but in addition, they also introduced a similar tool for text to Laura. So, let\'s say you have a set of really complex'

[32:03] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'instructions which you want to reuse again and again. For example, if you want to get the AI to write in a certain style or to do a certain task that requires multiple steps or specific output formats. Well, traditionally'

[32:15] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'again, you would have to keep copying and pasting these instructions into the AI or else it\'s going to forget after you chat with it for a long time. However, in this instance, you can just compact all your text instructions into a Laura and then feed it through this'

[32:29] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
